  "content": {
    "visible_text": "Dojo In Japanese, the word dojo means the place of the way. At Quantum, we strive to create a safe space for healing and self-actualization; a blank canvas for creating your journey. Our dojo is a large open space filled with natural light, right in the heart of San Francisco’s vibrant Mission District. With the help of … Read more Dojo Instructors Master Rachael Evans (she/her), is the founder and chief instructor at Quantum Martial Arts, with over 40 years of martial arts experience. A sixth-degree black belt, she teaches a unique style of her own creation that blends Tae Kwon Do, Wing Chun, Judo, and Arnis, among other styles, in a challenging and positive learning environment. Inspired by … Read more Instructors Schedule We offer martial arts classes for adults (ages 13+) nine times a week, martial arts classes for kids (ages 6–9) three times a week, martial arts classes for pre-K (ages 4–5) three times a week, and even martial arts classes for teens (ages 10–14) three times a week. We also host quarterly free community workshops, which are open to the … Read more Schedule About Us The Quantum Dojo is a nonprofit community studio offering martial arts classes for all ages focused on self-actualization, total body healing, and strength. Our goal is to help people tap into their potential, seeking balance and grace through movement, while establishing a strong foundation of integrity and self-discipline that will facilitate personal and professional success. In the spirit of this mission, we offer martial arts classes for adults and martial arts classes for kids , as well as community events such as rolling & falling for cyclists workshops and self-defense classes. Reviews Facebook Community Dojo Quantum Martial Arts is a registered 501(c)(3) nonprofit in the State of California, and we thrive on the generosity of people like you. All donations are tax-deductible. Quantum’s tax ID number is 26-1534597. No donation is too small, or too large. Whether it’s $20 or $20,000, every cent will be hugely appreciated and put to good use. Support Our Kids Donate now to support our youth scholarship program which allows families in need to train at reduced cost. We believe investment in our community involves investing in our youth. Our Sister Schools Our Seattle Dojo has served thousands of students since opening on Capitol Hill in 1995, and currently offers youth and adult classes in the Central District. Our Portland Dojo was established in 2020, and currently offers youth and adult classes in Southeast Portland. A WordPress.com Website .",
